comments.body:
@TomSweeneyRedHat, we should make it a PS in today's meeting to discuss a way forward. The problem we're hitting here is that go 1.13 starts to remove some obsolete files in ./vendor that previous versions did not remove.

Ultimately, I believe that we should have only _one_ CI job for vendoring using go 1.13. We somehow need to move to it at some point. However, as soon as we do that, contributors with go < 1.13 will face the problem that their `make vendor` will yield different results than what our CI wants. Hence, we could add a `make vendor-in-container` that executes `make vendor` in a `golang:1.13` container.

@rhatdan ^ hit the same issue last week.
